Do better.

Just giving 2 starts because the lady on the shake station Friday 6/20 at 9 pm was very nice and deserves a raise!!

editorialSummary.text: Family-friendly bowling alley with 32 lanes, a bar, lounge & grill, plus arcade games & pool tables.

text.text: We went to Aloma Bowl for Fathers Day and had such a great time! The atmosphere was fun and livelyperfect for a family outing. Bowling was a blast, and the ambience really made it feel special. Everything was clean, the staff was friendly and helpful, and there were plenty of interactive games to enjoy. Its definitely a great spot for families or anyone looking to have a good time. Highly recommend!

text.text: Aloma Bowl is the best! My husband and I frequent here, just ourselves or with a group of friends. We enjoy bowling and Aloma Bowl has friendly staff, plentiful lanes and a solid F&B menu. The food is delicious - cheese curds and tater tots are a must! The daily promotions are always great and the venue is kept clean. Ive done karaoke on a Friday night, which is held at the semi-private bar dining area. Weve gone to a few alleys around the area and Aloma Bowl is our favorite.

text.text: I grew up in this bowling alley I havent been in many years I thought it would be fun to bring my kids so we got an hour then we had like 20 minutes left sent our son up to pay for another hour and realized they charged $45. Their board made it look like they had it for $6.50 per hour per lane. We had no interest in paying that much for an hour. Apparently the board was just confusing and the 6.50. That I suppose is on us but a. That price is insane and b. Their board is definitely misleading. The thing that really made us mad is when we went up and said never mind on the second hour and the obliged and refunded but they also immediately cut off our lane when we had over 10 minutes left. This place is over priced as it is and now they are just taking our time from us. Im so frustrated. I grew up here. Its disappointing but Im going to have to find somewhere else to bowl.

text.text:
If I could give negative stars, I would. This place is an absolute disgrace to customer service and hospitality. From the moment we walked in, it was clear that cleanliness and professionalism are completely absent here. The bathroom was filthy, reeking of neglect and lacking basic hygiene. The lane we were assigned to was sticky, broken, and clearly hadnt been cleaned in ages. Disgusting doesnt even begin to cover it.

Now lets talk about the so-called server Heather. Ive been to many establishments and dealt with all kinds of staff, but Heather is hands down the rudest person Ive ever encountered in a customer-facing role. She was dismissive, hostile, and completely unprofessional. Its baffling how someone with experience in hospitality could treat paying customers with such blatant disrespect. Heather does NOT deserve to work with the public. Her attitude was appalling, and she made what should have been a fun outing feel hostile and uncomfortable.

As for the managerif you can even call him thathe didnt intervene once, even after the interaction was clearly escalating. In fact, it was obvious he was under the influencehigh as hell, slurring his words and completely unbothered by the chaos happening under his watch. He is not management material in the slightest. The lack of accountability and professionalism is beyond belief.

This place should be ashamed. The staff needs serious retrainingor replacing entirely. Until major changes are made, avoid this place at all costs. Youre better off staying home than subjecting yourself to this disaster.

text.text: Chick-fil-A never disappoints! Their chicken sandwiches are hands down the best in the fast-food world. The chicken is always perfectly seasoned, crispy on the outside, yet juicy and tender on the inside. The brioche bun is soft, buttery, and just the right amount of sweetness to balance the savory goodness of the chicken. The pickles are always fresh, adding that perfect zesty kick without overpowering the flavor. Whether it's a busy lunch or a late-night craving, Chick-fil-A consistently delivers top-quality sandwiches that leave me coming back for more. Simply unbeatable!
